request.description:
In order to use Suprema BioStar X API, you will need a Session ID which will be available after you’re logged in.

To log in, make a form encoded server side POST request as shown on example below.

`POST /api/login`

`Host: server_ip|domain_name[:port]`

`{“User”: {“login_id”: “user_login_id_here”, “password”: “password_here”}}`

The parameters are:

| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| login_id | String | Y | Your login ID |
| password | String | Y | Your password |

When successful, you will receive back the following response:

``` json
Status: 200 OK
bs-session-id: c52127fea7f645149083d04d89ad68e5
Content-Type: application/json;charset=UTF-8
{
  "User": {
    "user_id": "1",
    "name": "Administrator",
    "gender": "1",
    "email": "admin111@gmail.com",
