request.description:
This API is used to send user data to a device.

For example when you want to send user John data after credential update to FaceStation F2.

#### BODY Parameters:

| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| id | Number | Y | ID of the device |

#### Response Example:

``` json
{
  "DeviceResponse" : {
    "rows" : [ {
      "id" : "50362288",
      "code" : "0"
    } ],
    "result" : "true"
  },
  "Response" : {
    "code" : "0",
    "link" : "https://support.supremainc.com/en/support/home",
    "message" : "Success"
  }
}

```

#### Response Properties:

| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| DeviceResponse | Object | Response from device |
| DeviceResponse.rows | Array | List of device ID |
| DeviceResponse.result | Boolean | Indicate success or fail |
| Response | Object | Indicate success or fail |

#### Notes:

- Set `adv=mode1` on Query Parameter to enabled advanced search compatibility. This parameter is optional. When not used, it will use the previous capability.

- Request Body with Advanced Search example (see `Batch Edit with Advanced Search` for `adv_criteria` details) :


``` json
{
  "DeviceCollection" : {
    "rows" : [ {
      "id" : "50362288"
    } ]
  },
  "adv_criteria" : {
    "limit" : 50,
    "order_by" : "user_id:false",
    "user_group_ids" : [ 1014 ],
    "user_id" : "8",
    "user_email" : "support@supremainc.com"
  }
}

```

This API is used to fetch user information via advanced search.

#### BODY Parameters:

| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| limit | Number | N | The maximum number of users to return. Default is 50. |
| offset | String | N | The number of users to skip before starting to return results. Default is 0. |
| user_id | String | N | The User ID to search, supports like search |
| user_group_id | String | N | Group ID for search user. Also gets the child user group |
| user_group_ids | String | N | Array of Group IDs for advanced search parameter |
| user_name | String | N | User name for Advance Search parameter, supports like search both encrypted and unencrypted |
| user_email | String | N | User email, supports like search both encrypted and unencrypted |
| user_phone | String | N | User Phone for Advance Search parameter, supports like search both encrypted and unencrypted |
| user_department | String | N | User Department for Advance Search parameter, supports like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_access_group_ids | String | N | User access group id for advance search parameter, supports multiple value with format String with Delimiter , i.e 1,2,3.  <br>\* = User(s) who have any AG.  <br>void = User(s) who does not belong to any AG. |
| user_title | String | N | User title for advance search parameter, supports like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_card | String | N | User card ID |
| user_status | Boolean | N | User status for advance search parameter |
| user_operator_level_id | String | Y | User operator level id for Advance Search parameter |
| user_custom_field_1 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_2 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_3 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_4 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_5 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_6 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_7 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_8 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_9 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| user_custom_field_10 | String | N | Custom fields for advance search parameter support like search on unencrypted and exact search on encrypted |
| order_by | String | N | Order, will accept with format properties:false, for example if we want to order by name, it will be user_name:false. false = ASCENDING and true = DESCENDING |

