request.description:
This API is used to create multiple trigger actions.

#### BODY Parameters:

| **Parameter** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| name | String | Y | Enter a name of the trigger & action. |
| priority | Number | Y | Priority index of the trigger & action. |
| is_quick_action | Character | N | Fill with character “Y” or “N”. This parameter used to describe that the Trigger & Action can be use as a Quick Action |
| schedule:id | Number | Y | ID of the schedule which will be used by the trigger & action. |
| trigger:source_type | Number | Y | Select a device/door/zone at which a specific event will be monitored. Multiple devices/doors/zones can be selected. The devices/doors/zones work independently even when they are disconnected from the BioStar server.  <br>1=Device, 2=Door, 3=Zone |
| event_types:code | Number | Y | ID of the events which will trigger an action. At least one event must be selected.  <br>Event lists may be activated differently depending on the options selected in Device, Door, and Zone. |
| devices:id | Number | Y | Select a device which performs the action. You can select a device or BioStar X to perform an action. |
| doors:id | Number | Y | ID of the door which will trigger an action. |
| zones:id | Number | Y | ID of the zone which will trigger an action. |
| device_action_id:device_id:id | Number | Y | ID of the device which will perform an action. |
| device_action_id:relay_signal_id:id | Number | Y | Relay of the device which will be used to perform an action. |
| device_action_id:relay_index | Number | Y | Relay index of the device. |
| door_action:door_id:id | Number | Y | ID of the door which will perform an action |
| door_action:door_signal | Number | Y | Door signal as operation of an action. Value between 345 and 348 |
| email_action_id:recipients | Array String | Y | List email recipients which BioStar X will send notifications to. Use comma (,) to separate each email. |
| smtp_id:id | Number | Y | ID of the SMTP setting which will be used to send notification email. |

#### Response Example:

``` json
{
  "TriggerAction": {
    "name": "ta 1",
    "priority": "0",
    "trigger": {
      "source_type": "1"
    },
    "schedule_id": {
      "id": "1"
    },
    "action": {
      "id": "800001",
      "device_action_id": {
        "device_id": {
          "id": "50355260"
        },
        "relay_index": "0",
        "relay_signal_id": {
          "id": "1"
        }
      },
      "email_action_id": {
        "receipients": [
          "wawe@test.com"
        ]
      },
      "smtp_id": {
        "id": "1"
      }
    }
  },
  "Response": {
    "code": "0",
    "link": "https://support.supremainc.com/en/support/home",
    "message": "Success"
  }
}

```

#### Response Properties:

```
- Response : The web server response.
    - code : success/error code.
    - link : suprema link
    - message : success/error message

```

#### Errors:

- `400 Bad Request`: The request was malformed or missing required parameters.

- `401 Unauthorized`: The API key provided was invalid or missing.

- `404 Not Found`: The requested resource was not found.

- `500 Internal Server Error`: An unexpected error occurred on the server.

